One hundred ECDE teachers graduated on Monday after a two-year programme at the West Pokot County ECDE College, Aramaget.Governor Simon Kachapin (pictured) presided over the first graduation of the ECDE teachers.He said the county is building enough ECDE centres to employ the graduates. So far, the county has employed more than 800 teachers, most of whom are untrained, to enhance early childhood education. They are expected to receive training.Kachapin said his government has established more than 200 ECDE centers. He urged students finishing form four this year join the ECDE training college.